# Kerry Modra

**Kerry Joan Modra** [OAM](/Medal_of_the_Order_of_Australia) (née Golding; born 27 November 1973) is an Australian Paralympic [tandem cycling](/Tandem_bicycle) pilot. She was born in the New South Wales city of [Nowra](/Nowra,_New_South_Wales). Modra is renowned for her exceptional career as a pilot for visually impaired cyclists, particularly her late husband, [Kieran Modra](/Kieran_Modra). Her journey in the world of para-cycling is marked by significant achievements, personal challenges, and a deep commitment to the sport.

## Early Life and Introduction to Cycling

Kerry Joan Golding was born on 27 November 1973 in [Nowra, New South Wales](/Nowra,_New_South_Wales). Before her cycling career, she had only played [netball](/Netball). Her life took a significant turn when she met Kieran Modra, a visually impaired cyclist, at a friend's 21st birthday party. Kieran convinced her to take up cycling, and she soon became his pilot. This partnership would lead to a remarkable career in para-cycling.

## Cycling Career

### Paralympic Games

Modra's first major achievement came at the [1996 Atlanta Games](/1996_Summer_Paralympics), where she won a gold medal with Kieran Modra in the Mixed 200 m Sprint Tandem open event. This victory earned her a [Medal of the Order of Australia](/Order_of_Australia), recognizing her outstanding contribution to the sport.

At the [2000 Sydney Games](/2000_Summer_Paralympics), Modra faced personal challenges. She was pregnant with the couple's first child and fainted due to low blood pressure during a quarter-final sprint race. As a result, she was replaced as Kieran's pilot by his sister [Tania Modra](/Tania_Modra) for the rest of the games. Despite these challenges, Modra's dedication to the sport remained unwavering.

### UCI Para-cycling Track World Championships

Modra's success extended to the [UCI Para-cycling Track World Championships](/UCI_Para-cycling_Track_World_Championships). In 1998, at the championships held in [Colorado Springs](/Colorado_Springs), she won gold medals in the Mixed Tandem Sprint B, Mixed Tandem Time Trial B, and Mixed Individual Pursuit B events. These victories further solidified her reputation as a formidable pilot in the world of para-cycling.

## Personal Life

Kerry Modra was married to Kieran Modra from May 1997 until his death in 2019. The couple had three daughters. Kieran Modra, a highly decorated Paralympic cyclist, passed away in a cycling accident near Gawler, South Australia, in November 2019. His death was a significant loss to the cycling community and to Kerry, who had shared both personal and professional lives with him.

## Awards and Recognition

In addition to her [Medal of the Order of Australia](/Order_of_Australia), Modra received an [Australian Sports Medal](/Australian_Sports_Medal) in 2000. These awards reflect her significant contributions to Australian sports and her dedication to para-cycling.

## Legacy

Kerry Modra's career as a tandem cycling pilot is a testament to her skill, determination, and resilience. Her achievements at the Paralympic Games and the UCI Para-cycling Track World Championships have left a lasting impact on the sport. Despite personal challenges and the tragic loss of her husband, Modra's legacy continues to inspire athletes in the para-cycling community.